$ Python - time

{ sleep

  `time.sleep(secs)` stops execution of the script for `secs` seconds.

  gh|about-python|/standard-library/time/sleep.py||

}
{ perf_counter #py-time-perf_counter

  `time.perf_counter` allows to quickly measure the time something takes.

   gh|about-python|/standard-library/time/perf_counter.py||

   For more accurate timings, the → development/languages/Python/standard-library/timeit[`timeit` module] should probably be used.

}

